daily_summary.headline: SpaceX Starlink Launches and Aurora Opportunities Highlight the Day

top_events.title: Falcon 9 Block 5 | Starlink Group 17-19
top_events.description: SpaceX is set to launch a batch of 25 Starlink satellites into low Earth orbit. This mission supports the expansion of the Starlink internet constellation.
top_events.action: Watch live stream for launch details.

top_events.title: Aurora Viewing Opportunity
top_events.description: A G1 geomagnetic storm may provide aurora visibility at high latitudes, particularly above 65째 latitude.
top_events.action: Check local conditions and prepare for aurora viewing.

top_events.title: Electron | Bridging The Swarm (NeonSat-1A)
top_events.description: Rocket Lab's Electron rocket is scheduled to launch the NeonSat-1A, testing constellation capabilities for Earth observation.
